title: Munich Pact - 1938 | Today In History | 30 Sept 17
description:
On September 30, 1938, British, French, German and Italian leaders agreed at a meeting in Munich that Nazi Germany would be allowed to annex Czechoslovakia's Sudetenland.


Scenes of the meeting between Adolf Hitler, Benito Mussolini and Neville Chamberlain before the outbreak of the Second World War.
